package aperture

import prepositional.*

// An entity which can be opened, scoping access to its contents: a file for streaming access,
// a directory as a root for filesystem operations, or an archive or document read through its
// entries. An instance is written `target is Openable in Form by Flag to Handle`, in the same
// way that a value may be `Decodable in Json`. The form вҖ” what the target is opened *as* вҖ”
// drives instance selection at the use site, since one path may be openable `in File` form,
// `in Directory` form or `in Zip` form; `Operand` is the flag type admissible for that
// target/form pair; and `Result`, intersected with `Granting` of the mode's grants, is
// provided contextually for the duration of the block. Handles are expected to be
// capabilities, confined to the block by capture checking.
trait Openable extends Typeclass, Formal, Operable, Resultant:
  def open[grants <: Grant, result]
    ( value: Self, mode: Mode granting grants, flags: List[Operand] )
    ( block: ((Result & Granting[grants])^) ?=> result )
  :   result
